	abstract = {Structured continuous vacuum-ultraviolet emission from selectively excited rotational-vibrational levels of H2 in the B 2p 1Σu+and C 2p 1Σu+electronic states was investigated spectroscopically. Spontaneous radiative dissociation of H2 (B, C) molecules occurs via B, C → X bound-free emission. The C → X emission continuum and the effect of centrifugal distortion on the B → X continuum were observed for the first time. © {IOP} Publishing Ltd.},
